        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Pherusa aspera (Stimpson, 1854). A. Neotype (USNM 8889), anterior region, dorsal view. B. Same, ventral view. C. Another specimen (USNM 8957), head, frontal view (branchiae and palps removed; BS: branchial scar, LL: lateral lip, PS: palp scar). D. Neotype, chaetiger 10, right notopodium (inset: chaetal tips). E. Same, chaetiger 9, neurochaetae (two smaller neurochaetae not shown). Scale bars: A, C: 0.7 mm, B: 0.9 mm, D: 225 µm, E: 112 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4951900/files/figure.png" .

